{/* # BLS ImageToText Task */}

with this `POST` request you can solve BLS Captcha image challenges.

```
POST https://api.nocaptchaai.com/createTask
Host: api.nocaptchaai.com
Content-Type: application/json
```

### Request Format

```json
{
    "clientKey": "YOUR_API_KEY", // your nocaptchaai apikey
    "task": {
        "type": "ImageToTextTask", // task type
        "module": "bls", // module name for specific captcha
        "images": [
            "/9j/4AAQSkZJRgABAQAAAQABAAD/", // base64 image
            "/9j/4AAQSkZJRgABAQAAAQABAAD/", // base64 image
            "/9j/4AAQSkZJRgABAQAAAQABAAD/",
            "/9j/4AAQSkZJRgABAQAAAQABAAD/",
            "/9j/4AAQSkZJRgABAQAAAQABAAD/",
            "/9j/4AAQSkZJRgABAQAAAQABAAD/",
            "/9j/4AAQSkZJRgABAQAAAQABAAD/",
            "/9j/4AAQSkZJRgABAQAAAQABAAD/",
            "/9j/4AAQSkZJRgABAQAAAQABAAD/", // base64 image
        ],
        "numeric": true, // if solution is number form
        "case": false, // if solution needs to be upper or lower
        "maxLength": 3 // 
    }
}
```

### Request Example

```json
{
  "clientKey": "userxx-2782xx2-065e-x-7daa-xxxxx",
  "task": {
    "type": "ImageToTextTask",
    "images": [
      "",
      "",
      "",
      "",
      "",
      "",
      "",
      "",
      ""
    ],
    "numeric": true,
    "module": "morocco",
    "case": false,
    "maxLength": 3
  }
}
```

  <TabItem label="Go">
    ```go
package main

import (
	"bytes"
	"encoding/json"
	"fmt"
	"net/http"
)

const url = "https://api.nocaptchaai.com/createTask"

type Task struct {
Type string `json:"type"`
Images []string `json:"images"`
Numeric bool `json:"numeric"`
Module string `json:"module"`
Case bool `json:"case"`
MaxLength int `json:"maxLength"`
}

type Payload struct {
ClientKey string `json:"clientKey"`
Task Task `json:"task"`
}

func main() {
payload := Payload{
ClientKey: "userxx-2782xx2-065e-x-7daa-xxxxx",
Task: Task{
Type: "ImageToTextTask",
Images: []string{
"/9j/4AAQSkZJRgABAQAAAQABAAD/2wBD",
"/9j/4AAQSkZJRgABAQAAAQABAAD/2wBD",
"/9j/4AAQSkZJRgABAQAAAQABAAD/2wBD",
"/9j/4AAQSkZJRgABAQAAAQABAAD/2wBD",
"/9j/4AAQSkZJRgABAQAAAQABAAD/2wBD",
"/9j/4AAQSkZJRgABAQAAAQABAAD/2wBD",
"/9j/4AAQSkZJRgABAQAAAQABAAD/2wBD",
"/9j/4AAQSkZJRgABAQAAAQABAAD/2wBD",
"/9j/4AAQSkZJRgABAQAAAQABAAD/2wBD",
},
Numeric: true,
Module: "morocco",
Case: false,
MaxLength: 3,
},
}

    jsonData, err := json.Marshal(payload)
    if err != nil {
    	fmt.Println("Error marshaling JSON:", err)
    	return
    }

    req, err := http.NewRequest("POST", url, bytes.NewBuffer(jsonData))
    if err != nil {
    	fmt.Println("Error creating request:", err)
    	return
    }
    req.Header.Set("Content-Type", "application/json")

    client := &http.Client{}
    resp, err := client.Do(req)
    if err != nil {
    	fmt.Println("Error making request:", err)
    	return
    }
    defer resp.Body.Close()

    var result map[string]interface{}
    if err := json.NewDecoder(resp.Body).Decode(&result); err != nil {
    	fmt.Println("Error decoding response:", err)
    	return
    }

    solution, exists := result["solution"]
    if exists {
    	fmt.Println("Solution:", solution)
    } else {
    	fmt.Println("No solution found")
    }

}

````

    <TabItem label="C#">
    ```csharp
using System;
using System.Collections.Generic;
using System.Net.Http;
using System.Text;
using System.Text.Json;
using System.Threading.Tasks;

class Program
{
    private static readonly string url = "https://api.nocaptchaai.com/createTask";

    class TaskData
    {
        public string Type { get; set; } = "ImageToTextTask";
        public List<string> Images { get; set; }
        public bool Numeric { get; set; } = true;
        public string Module { get; set; } = "morocco";
        public bool Case { get; set; } = false;
        public int MaxLength { get; set; } = 3;
    }

    class Payload
    {
        public string ClientKey { get; set; } = "userxx-2782xx2-065e-x-7daa-xxxxx";
        public TaskData Task { get; set; }
    }

    static async Task Main()
    {
        var payload = new Payload
        {
            Task = new TaskData
            {
                Images = new List<string>
                {
                    "/9j/4AAQSkZJRgABAQAAAQABAAD/2wBD",
                    "/9j/4AAQSkZJRgABAQAAAQABAAD/2wBD",
                    "/9j/4AAQSkZJRgABAQAAAQABAAD/2wBD",
                    "/9j/4AAQSkZJRgABAQAAAQABAAD/2wBD",
                    "/9j/4AAQSkZJRgABAQAAAQABAAD/2wBD",
                    "/9j/4AAQSkZJRgABAQAAAQABAAD/2wBD",
                    "/9j/4AAQSkZJRgABAQAAAQABAAD/2wBD",
                    "/9j/4AAQSkZJRgABAQAAAQABAAD/2wBD",
                    "/9j/4AAQSkZJRgABAQAAAQABAAD/2wBD"
                }
            }
        };

        var jsonData = JsonSerializer.Serialize(payload);
        using var client = new HttpClient();
        var content = new StringContent(jsonData, Encoding.UTF8, "application/json");

        try
        {
            var response = await client.PostAsync(url, content);
            response.EnsureSuccessStatusCode();

            var responseBody = await response.Content.ReadAsStringAsync();
            var result = JsonSerializer.Deserialize<Dictionary<string, object>>(responseBody);

            if (result != null && result.ContainsKey("solution"))
            {
                Console.WriteLine("Solution: " + result["solution"]);
            }
            else
            {
                Console.WriteLine("No solution found");
            }
        }
        catch (Exception ex)
        {
            Console.WriteLine("Error: " + ex.Message);
        }
    }
}

````

<TabItem label="Rust">
    ```rust
use reqwest::Client;
use serde::{Deserialize, Serialize};
use tokio;

#[derive(Serialize)]
struct TaskData { #[serde(rename = "type")]
task_type: String,
images: Vec<String>,
numeric: bool,
module: String,
case: bool,
max_length: u8,
}

#[derive(Serialize)]
struct Payload {
client_key: String,
task: TaskData,
}

#[derive(Deserialize)]
struct ResponseData {
solution: Option<String>,
}

#[tokio::main]
async fn main() {
let url = "https://api.nocaptchaai.com/createTask";
let payload = Payload {
client_key: "userxx-2782xx2-065e-x-7daa-xxxxx".to_string(),
task: TaskData {
task_type: "ImageToTextTask".to_string(),
images: vec![
                "/9j/4AAQSkZJRgABAQAAAQABAAD/2wBD".to_string(),
                "/9j/4AAQSkZJRgABAQAAAQABAAD/2wBD".to_string(),
                "/9j/4AAQSkZJRgABAQAAAQABAAD/2wBD".to_string(),
                "/9j/4AAQSkZJRgABAQAAAQABAAD/2wBD".to_string(),
                "/9j/4AAQSkZJRgABAQAAAQABAAD/2wBD".to_string(),
                "/9j/4AAQSkZJRgABAQAAAQABAAD/2wBD".to_string(),
                "/9j/4AAQSkZJRgABAQAAAQABAAD/2wBD".to_string(),
                "/9j/4AAQSkZJRgABAQAAAQABAAD/2wBD".to_string(),
                "/9j/4AAQSkZJRgABAQAAAQABAAD/2wBD".to_string(),
            ],
numeric: true,
module: "morocco".to_string(),
case: false,
max_length: 3,
},
};

    let client = Client::new();
    match client.post(url)
        .json(&payload)
        .send()
        .await {
        Ok(response) => {
            match response.json::<ResponseData>().await {
                Ok(parsed_response) => {
                    match parsed_response.solution {
                        Some(solution) => println!("Solution: {}", solution),
                        None => println!("No solution found"),
                    }
                }
                Err(_) => println!("Failed to parse response"),
            }
        }
        Err(_) => println!("Request failed"),
    }

}
